Yunnan: Standardizing the Management of Public Welfare Posts in Rural Areas-Xinhua News
Xinhua News Agency Kunming, December 12th (reporter Lin Bifeng): To continue providing employment assistance to people lifted out of poverty, consolidate and extend poverty relief results, Yunnan Province recently released policies related to the management of public welfare posts that facilitate rural revitalization, to help drive comprehensive rural revitalization.
A responsible person from the Yunnan Provincial Human Resources and Social Security Bureau introduced that at present a total of 448,300 rural public-benefit posts have been developed in Yunnan for the employment of rural people in difficulty such as poverty-stricken laborers, thereby playing an important role in helping the poverty-stricken group to realize increase in income through employment, consolidate the achievements of poverty alleviation and effectively improve the abilities of various public services in the countryside.
This new regulation was jointly issued by seven departments, including the Yunnan Human Resources and Social Security Department, Rural Revitalization Department, and Finance Department, mainly regulating the target scope, fund management, post development, and post management of grassroots public welfare post personnel recruitment.
In terms of position development and setting up, the new regulations are clear: positions are set up according to the principle of "post allocation based on demand, staffing according to post, dynamic management, overall limit control", "who develops, who uses and who is responsible for it" and "one post for one person, voluntary openness, unified management".
The recruitment process must be carried out in accordance with the steps of announcement, application, review, public announcement, appointment, pre-job training and arrangement to take up the post.
In addition, the new regulations have clearly specified the specific duties of the main development departments for rural public service posts, the subsidy standards and subsidy methods for rural public service posts, and have stipulated that the development departments for rural public service posts should purchase accidental injury commercial insurance for personnel appointed for rural public service posts; and require relevant departments to regularly supervise payment of subsidies for rural public service posts.
